1
00:00:00,001 --> 00:00:30,001
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .club, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

2
00:00:39,145 --> 00:00:40,675
(All characters, places,
and organizations are fictional.)

3
00:00:40,675 --> 00:00:41,975
(Children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:45,885 --> 00:00:47,955
(Episode 2)

5
00:00:48,015 --> 00:00:50,785
(Nua General Hospital)

6
00:00:50,855 --> 00:00:56,325
(Nua General Hospital)

7
00:00:56,395 --> 00:00:59,135
(Nua General Hospital)

8
00:01:37,135 --> 00:01:39,275
(Ha Yong Joong...)

9
00:01:39,535 --> 00:01:42,475
(is in the director's office.)

10
00:01:48,115 --> 00:01:50,345
- When did you get here?
- What happened to Momo?

11
00:01:51,145 --> 00:01:53,685
- Who told you?
- Does it matter who told me?

12
00:01:55,355 --> 00:01:56,355
The bends?

13
00:01:57,025 --> 00:01:58,625
She's almost recovered,
thanks to oxygen therapy.

14
00:01:59,325 --> 00:02:00,325
What's her room number?

15
00:02:00,895 --> 00:02:02,195
She's not seeing anyone but her mom.

16
00:02:02,665 --> 00:02:04,065
She doesn't want anyone
to see her without makeup.

17
00:02:05,065 --> 00:02:06,065
She's an actress, you know.

18
00:02:47,935 --> 00:02:49,945
This snowman is too risqué.

19
00:05:39,575 --> 00:05:42,415
(Six Months Before Momo's Accident)

20
00:07:01,795 --> 00:07:02,795
Yong Joong.

21
00:07:03,795 --> 00:07:05,695
Have I changed that much...

22
00:07:05,695 --> 00:07:06,935
that you don't even recognize me?

23
00:07:09,905 --> 00:07:12,005
I guess I haven't
crossed your mind at all.

24
00:07:53,845 --> 00:07:56,185
Confirm the facts, post the headline,
then write the full article.

25
00:07:59,385 --> 00:08:01,585
(Sungwoo Daily: Pop Star A
to Release New Collab with Global Artist)

26
00:08:17,435 --> 00:08:19,035
Let's see...

27
00:08:19,935 --> 00:08:21,575
how the article turned out.

28
00:08:23,275 --> 00:08:25,475
(Sungwoo Daily)

29
00:08:44,395 --> 00:08:45,395
Why isn't it here?

30
00:08:55,005 --> 00:08:56,175
The article didn't run?

31
00:08:56,605 --> 00:08:57,845
It's running in the weekend edition.

32
00:08:58,145 --> 00:08:59,615
The weekend edition?

33
00:09:24,765 --> 00:09:26,605
Act like men, you punks!

34
00:09:26,935 --> 00:09:28,605
And stop picking on weaker kids.

35
00:09:31,845 --> 00:09:32,845
You punk...

36
00:09:37,315 --> 00:09:38,745
Some guy develops one game...

37
00:09:39,455 --> 00:09:40,915
and makes 100 million dollars.

38
00:09:42,555 --> 00:09:43,855
I can't even wrap my head around it.

39
00:09:44,425 --> 00:09:45,925
- One hundred million dollars?
- Who?

40
00:09:46,025 --> 00:09:47,795
Ha Yong Joong.
The guy who created "Lost Knights."

41
00:09:48,325 --> 00:09:51,295
- That's got to be an exaggeration.
- No, it's true.

42
00:09:51,295 --> 00:09:53,095
(Ha Yong Joong,
Developer of the Mega-hit "Lost Knights")

43
00:09:53,095 --> 00:09:54,295
That's insane.

44
00:10:00,075 --> 00:10:01,075
Move out.

45
00:10:07,815 --> 00:10:11,085
- I've gone up an inch, haven't I?
- You still have a model's physique.

46
00:10:14,055 --> 00:10:15,655
There's a stack of paintings in my room.

47
00:10:15,655 --> 00:10:16,825
It's next to my desk.

48
00:10:17,125 --> 00:10:18,125
Got it.

49
00:10:19,995 --> 00:10:21,025
Is she new?

50
00:10:21,225 --> 00:10:22,925
Momo's new stylist. She started last week.

51
00:10:29,965 --> 00:10:31,405
This isn't a fake, is it?

52
00:10:33,375 --> 00:10:35,435
Paul Kim. You've never heard of him?

53
00:10:36,175 --> 00:10:37,945
I was told he's an artist
who was based in Germany.

54
00:10:38,505 --> 00:10:41,245
Did you buy it directly from the artist?

55
00:10:53,555 --> 00:10:57,395
("Scene within You," Paul Kim)

56
00:11:04,565 --> 00:11:08,005
(Passenger Terminal One)

57
00:11:09,445 --> 00:11:11,775
(Bus Stop)

58
00:11:19,385 --> 00:11:21,785
Judging by your luggage,
I take it you've been living abroad.

59
00:11:23,255 --> 00:11:24,255
Yes.

60
00:11:24,885 --> 00:11:25,885
Whereabouts?

61
00:11:27,355 --> 00:11:28,595
(Republic of Korea Passport)

62
00:11:45,605 --> 00:11:46,645
Hello.

63
00:11:47,315 --> 00:11:49,275
The article was very well-written.

64
00:11:49,915 --> 00:11:50,945
Thank you.

65
00:11:59,225 --> 00:12:00,525
Do you need help with anything?

66
00:12:01,325 --> 00:12:03,065
No, I'm good. You can head home.

67
00:12:18,275 --> 00:12:21,275
Hello. Didn't you get the message?

68
00:12:21,645 --> 00:12:24,615
My father in the US suddenly passed away,

69
00:12:24,945 --> 00:12:27,985
so our reporter, Geum Ba Ra,
went to the interview in my place.

70
00:12:37,025 --> 00:12:38,165
(Ha Yong Joong,
Developer of the Mega-hit "Lost Knights")

71
00:12:42,765 --> 00:12:45,365
(Geum Ba Ra, Culture Desk Reporter)

72
00:12:48,605 --> 00:12:49,605
Bow!

73
00:12:50,845 --> 00:12:51,845
Ready for sparring!

74
00:12:53,015 --> 00:12:55,145
Sparring, begin!

75
00:13:15,635 --> 00:13:16,705
(Sungwoo Daily)

76
00:13:18,365 --> 00:13:20,135
(Geum Ba Ra,
Culture Desk Reporter, Sungwoo Daily)

77
00:13:27,775 --> 00:13:31,045
(Sungwoo Daily)

78
00:13:44,965 --> 00:13:46,025
This is Ha Yong Joong.

79
00:13:46,095 --> 00:13:47,565
I was wondering if you were...

80
00:13:47,565 --> 00:13:50,305
the Geum Ba Ra in the fourth grade
at Minjin Elementary 16 years ago.

81
00:13:58,305 --> 00:14:00,315
Yes, that's me. Yong Joong.

82
00:14:10,255 --> 00:14:11,325
Yes, I am.

83
00:14:15,955 --> 00:14:17,025
Can you talk now?

84
00:14:26,335 --> 00:14:28,275
I'll call you in about ten minutes.

85
00:14:40,115 --> 00:14:41,215
(Geum Ba Ra)

86
00:14:43,785 --> 00:14:44,825
Hello?

87
00:14:46,125 --> 00:14:47,225
Hello?

88
00:14:47,225 --> 00:14:48,755
Look at you, all grown up.

89
00:14:49,025 --> 00:14:50,025
Amazing.

90
00:14:52,465 --> 00:14:54,695
Why didn't you say anything yesterday?
You totally played dumb.

91
00:14:55,365 --> 00:14:56,965
We were meeting for work.

92
00:14:57,235 --> 00:14:58,865
So you're saying you knew it was me?

93
00:15:00,305 --> 00:15:01,805
How could I forget?

94
00:15:02,475 --> 00:15:03,475
Yes.

95
00:15:03,475 --> 00:15:05,345
The nerve! If I were with you now...

96
00:15:06,745 --> 00:15:08,215
If I were with me now?

97
00:15:09,015 --> 00:15:10,115
I'd give you a noogie.

98
00:15:10,585 --> 00:15:13,515
I thought I was texting
with Kim Jeong Ah the whole time.

99
00:15:13,785 --> 00:15:15,015
I figured as much.

100
00:15:15,285 --> 00:15:17,485
I just can't believe it.
How could that little kid...

101
00:15:19,455 --> 00:15:21,395
- I haven't changed, have I?
- Not at all.

102
00:15:21,395 --> 00:15:23,765
An Hee hasn't aged a day either.

103
00:15:24,395 --> 00:15:26,465
- How is he?
- He's doing well.

104
00:15:26,535 --> 00:15:28,665
- Have you married?
- No.

105
00:15:28,795 --> 00:15:30,265
Let's meet up and talk.
You're off work, right?

106
00:15:30,935 --> 00:15:31,965
I'm about to leave now.

107
00:15:32,365 --> 00:15:34,475
We have to meet tonight.
If you're busy, we can meet later.

108
00:15:34,475 --> 00:15:35,475
Bring An Hee.

109
00:15:35,975 --> 00:15:37,245
I don't have any other plans.

110
00:15:37,945 --> 00:15:39,575
I'll try calling An Hee.

111
00:15:39,675 --> 00:15:41,515
What foods do you like? I'll book a table.

112
00:15:56,225 --> 00:15:59,295
Okay, just act natural,
like you're having a conversation.

113
00:16:01,295 --> 00:16:03,735
Could you give me a little smile?

114
00:16:04,665 --> 00:16:06,065
Great.

115
00:16:07,105 --> 00:16:09,705
You're kidding, right?
About never having been to Paris.

116
00:16:10,745 --> 00:16:11,745
I'm serious.

117
00:16:12,945 --> 00:16:14,445
I've never even been
on an international flight.

118
00:16:15,075 --> 00:16:17,015
I spent all four years of college
working part-time jobs.

119
00:16:18,385 --> 00:16:19,385
Yes, great.

120
00:16:20,015 --> 00:16:21,315
Okay, could you stand up for a moment?

121
00:16:25,125 --> 00:16:26,755
I thought you grew up like a princess.

122
00:16:27,525 --> 00:16:28,525
I was wrong about you.

123
00:16:31,425 --> 00:16:32,565
Would you like to take a look?

124
00:16:34,295 --> 00:16:36,635
I can delete them if you want.

125
00:16:36,635 --> 00:16:38,165
If it's not going to run, why bother?

126
00:16:40,605 --> 00:16:42,005
Could you send them to my phone?

127
00:17:13,135 --> 00:17:14,635
I can still see the little kid
you used to be.

128
00:17:22,175 --> 00:17:24,985
I can't get a hold of An Hee.
He might be working.

129
00:17:25,045 --> 00:17:27,115
What does he do for work?
He can't even answer your call?

130
00:17:28,055 --> 00:17:29,085
Take a guess.

131
00:17:29,585 --> 00:17:31,185
I just know that he joined the UDT.

132
00:17:31,885 --> 00:17:34,495
Was he able to complete the UDT
with his personality?

133
00:17:34,495 --> 00:17:35,555
He did.

134
00:17:35,625 --> 00:17:37,195
So, did he get a corporate job?

135
00:17:37,195 --> 00:17:38,895
He's a bodyguard for some chairman.

136
00:17:39,125 --> 00:17:40,135
A bodyguard?

137
00:17:40,935 --> 00:17:42,765
That suits him.
It's the perfect job for him.

138
00:17:48,375 --> 00:17:50,045
Order whatever you want.

139
00:17:53,175 --> 00:17:56,315
The course menu here is nice, isn't it?
And the portions aren't too big.

140
00:17:56,445 --> 00:17:57,885
- The tasting menu?
- Yes.

141
00:17:58,415 --> 00:17:59,855
- And for wine...
- Let's save the wine...

142
00:17:59,855 --> 00:18:01,115
for next time with An Hee.

143
00:18:01,585 --> 00:18:03,225
- Okay.
- And how would you like your steak?

144
00:18:03,555 --> 00:18:06,425
- Medium, please.
- Maybe I'll get the fish so we can share?

145
00:18:06,795 --> 00:18:09,355
- How about the sea perch with caviar?
- Yes.

146
00:18:13,665 --> 00:18:14,965
Let's toast with our water then.

147
00:18:21,235 --> 00:18:22,735
Am I dreaming, or is this real?

148
00:18:23,805 --> 00:18:25,845
It feels like the impossible has happened.

149
00:18:27,115 --> 00:18:28,745
Are you leaving for Italy tomorrow?

150
00:18:28,875 --> 00:18:31,615
I was supposed to leave today,
but I changed my flight to see you.

151
00:18:32,315 --> 00:18:33,315
Goodness.

152
00:18:34,155 --> 00:18:35,415
When did you get so tall?

153
00:18:36,825 --> 00:18:38,755
Starting in sixth grade.

154
00:18:50,535 --> 00:18:52,165
You were just a little kid.

155
00:18:53,375 --> 00:18:55,905
Are you disappointed
I'm not that little kid anymore?

156
00:18:56,135 --> 00:18:58,845
Not disappointed, it's amazing!

157
00:18:58,845 --> 00:19:01,315
You were barely kindergarten-sized
with the face of a four-year-old.

158
00:19:02,945 --> 00:19:04,315
I was really insecure about that.

159
00:19:04,985 --> 00:19:06,615
I was insecure about everything, though.

160
00:19:07,385 --> 00:19:08,915
Especially my height...

161
00:19:11,785 --> 00:19:12,955
Would it be okay to ask...

162
00:19:13,925 --> 00:19:14,955
something like this?

163
00:19:17,425 --> 00:19:19,265
Did you end up getting adopted?

164
00:19:21,935 --> 00:19:24,605
I was about to be, but it fell through.

165
00:19:24,935 --> 00:19:27,105
- Why?
- It's a long story.

166
00:19:28,575 --> 00:19:31,275
There was another kid
you always used to hang out with.

167
00:19:31,545 --> 00:19:34,345
- Jin Ju. Kim Jin Ju.
- Right, what's she up to?

168
00:19:35,015 --> 00:19:37,185
She studied fashion design
and works in the field.

169
00:19:37,745 --> 00:19:38,985
Sounds like everyone's doing well.

170
00:19:46,425 --> 00:19:47,625
You have a boyfriend, right?

171
00:19:49,125 --> 00:19:51,065
What makes you think I do?

172
00:19:51,665 --> 00:19:53,695
I was deliberately
holding back that question.

173
00:19:54,865 --> 00:19:57,205
Are you seeing someone?

174
00:19:57,465 --> 00:19:58,735
Why were you deliberately avoiding it?

175
00:19:59,135 --> 00:20:01,405
I was worried you'd get the wrong idea
and think I was interested.

176
00:20:02,005 --> 00:20:03,505
Using the interview as an excuse.

177
00:20:04,745 --> 00:20:07,315
I was completely honest with my answers.

178
00:20:07,815 --> 00:20:09,275
I never even had the time to date anyone.

179
00:20:10,745 --> 00:20:12,915
But you have plenty of time now, right?

180
00:20:12,915 --> 00:20:14,985
If someone catches my eye, why not?

181
00:20:16,085 --> 00:20:17,985
Are you trying to set me up with someone?

182
00:20:21,125 --> 00:20:22,755
Tell me what you're looking for.

183
00:20:23,265 --> 00:20:24,295
What do you mean?

184
00:20:25,125 --> 00:20:26,395
I'll start thinking about it now.

185
00:20:27,135 --> 00:20:28,195
No reporters, though.

186
00:20:28,465 --> 00:20:29,635
What's wrong with reporters?

187
00:20:30,265 --> 00:20:31,805
You're saying that to a reporter.

188
00:20:31,935 --> 00:20:34,375
You're family first, not a reporter.

189
00:20:42,545 --> 00:20:43,885
So where are you living now?

190
00:20:44,585 --> 00:20:46,115
In a multi-unit house in Myeongil-dong.

191
00:20:46,115 --> 00:20:47,185
It's about 46m².

192
00:20:48,015 --> 00:20:50,325
- By yourself?
- Yes, of course.

193
00:20:50,455 --> 00:20:52,055
What about An Hee? Is he seeing anyone?

194
00:20:53,085 --> 00:20:56,225
He was almost Prince Charming,
but it didn't work out.

195
00:20:56,595 --> 00:20:57,695
Her family was against it?

196
00:20:58,465 --> 00:20:59,625
After his UDT service,

197
00:20:59,825 --> 00:21:01,835
he was a bodyguard
for a conglomerate heiress,

198
00:21:02,365 --> 00:21:04,705
and the heiress he was protecting
fell for him.

199
00:21:04,765 --> 00:21:06,335
A pretty princess or an ugly one?

200
00:21:06,405 --> 00:21:07,975
Come on.

201
00:21:08,035 --> 00:21:11,105
An Hee is picky about looks,
so she must have been pretty.

202
00:21:11,845 --> 00:21:12,845
So what happened?

203
00:21:12,975 --> 00:21:15,345
The heiress even decided
she wanted to marry him,

204
00:21:15,915 --> 00:21:17,085
so he got fired.

205
00:21:22,355 --> 00:21:23,355
Hey.

206
00:21:23,555 --> 00:21:24,785
Liven up the mood a little.

207
00:21:27,255 --> 00:21:28,495
You, sit down.

208
00:21:41,075 --> 00:21:42,505
I'm sorry, Staff Sergeant.

209
00:21:43,205 --> 00:21:44,345
I had no other choice.

210
00:21:50,315 --> 00:21:52,485
When your commander is getting humiliated
in front of his men,

211
00:21:53,555 --> 00:21:55,055
it'd be a dereliction of duty
to stand there and watch.

212
00:21:55,485 --> 00:21:56,615
Now that you're here, have a drink.

213
00:21:57,785 --> 00:21:59,025
I'm not much of a drinker, but...

214
00:22:11,435 --> 00:22:12,935
Get in, Little Reporter.

215
00:22:19,305 --> 00:22:21,645
- Where are we going?
- Don't ask.

216
00:22:22,915 --> 00:22:25,245
We'll go to An Hee's place later.

217
00:22:25,915 --> 00:22:28,355
It's 30 minutes away.
Or 10 minutes if there's no traffic.

218
00:22:30,825 --> 00:22:33,225
The more I think about it,
you're really something else.

219
00:22:33,725 --> 00:22:35,755
How did you manage
not to show any emotion?

220
00:22:36,455 --> 00:22:38,095
Do you know what I was thinking?

221
00:22:40,665 --> 00:22:41,865
"Should I try to hit on her?"

222
00:22:44,405 --> 00:22:47,105
I was so happy to see you and so proud,

223
00:22:47,635 --> 00:22:48,735
but on the other hand,

224
00:22:51,145 --> 00:22:52,145
it's kind of a shame.

225
00:22:54,215 --> 00:22:56,715
If I hadn't recognized you
and made a move,

226
00:22:57,715 --> 00:23:00,515
would you have pretended not to know me
and just played along?

227
00:23:01,755 --> 00:23:02,915
Of course not.

228
00:23:03,785 --> 00:23:05,755
What do you mean, "of course not?"

229
00:23:06,085 --> 00:23:08,095
Come on,
I know you don't really mean that.

230
00:23:08,755 --> 00:23:09,855
I'm not just saying that.

231
00:23:10,865 --> 00:23:11,865
You're joking.

232
00:23:12,765 --> 00:23:15,095
What if I'm not joking
or just flattering you?

233
00:23:18,305 --> 00:23:19,665
How should I put it?

234
00:23:20,205 --> 00:23:22,735
As they say these days,
"Insanely charming."

235
00:23:24,045 --> 00:23:27,475
You're sharp and articulate,
but also polite and refined.

236
00:23:28,115 --> 00:23:30,285
And yet, you're completely unreadable.

237
00:23:32,545 --> 00:23:34,355
That sounds more like you.

238
00:23:34,715 --> 00:23:35,715
You think so?

239
00:23:36,555 --> 00:23:37,985
What about hiding your emotions?

240
00:23:40,555 --> 00:23:42,495
It's not on purpose.

241
00:23:42,625 --> 00:23:45,125
My environment forced me to be that way.

242
00:23:49,835 --> 00:23:51,365
I'm not saying you're jaded.

243
00:23:54,535 --> 00:23:55,535
Thank you.

244
00:23:57,275 --> 00:23:58,745
I really want to thank the skies...

245
00:23:59,275 --> 00:24:00,945
for helping you grow up safe and sound.

246
00:24:04,485 --> 00:24:06,185
Have you ever thought of me?

247
00:24:07,415 --> 00:24:08,415
Of course I did.

248
00:24:10,015 --> 00:24:11,385
Whenever I thought of An Hee.

249
00:24:14,255 --> 00:24:15,995
What about you? Did you think of me?

250
00:24:18,165 --> 00:24:19,995
- I did.
- Really?

251
00:24:22,135 --> 00:24:24,365
That punk, An Hee.
Should I go rough him up?

252
00:24:26,135 --> 00:24:27,375
He's a bodyguard.

253
00:24:28,575 --> 00:24:31,005
I can hold my own in a fight.
We're an even match.

254
00:24:31,075 --> 00:24:33,375
We were the top dogs together,
and we ran the Isu neighborhood.

255
00:24:35,145 --> 00:24:37,285
Why'd you drop out of high school?

256
00:24:37,585 --> 00:24:40,015
I was better at brawling
than I was at studying.

257
00:24:40,315 --> 00:24:42,155
I didn't exactly drop out. I got expelled.

258
00:24:43,255 --> 00:24:45,585
What's with the sour face?
You already knew.

259
00:24:48,725 --> 00:24:49,725
Hey, kiddo.

260
00:24:50,365 --> 00:24:51,565
You look even prettier when you smile.

261
00:24:53,895 --> 00:24:55,035
Yong Joong.

262
00:24:55,765 --> 00:24:57,135
I missed you.

263
00:24:58,205 --> 00:24:59,205
So, so much.

264
00:25:00,165 --> 00:25:01,675
I was desperate to see you again.

265
00:25:08,445 --> 00:25:09,545
Dear deity,

266
00:25:10,945 --> 00:25:12,115
did you finally answer...

267
00:25:12,985 --> 00:25:14,255
my prayer?

268
00:25:19,255 --> 00:25:21,555
Do you still play the double bass?

269
00:25:39,805 --> 00:25:41,015
I see marriage in your future.

270
00:25:41,945 --> 00:25:42,975
You're going to get married.

271
00:25:43,915 --> 00:25:45,845
- When?
- Within five years.

272
00:25:47,155 --> 00:25:48,285
But...

273
00:25:49,255 --> 00:25:50,855
your bride will be quite young.

274
00:25:52,355 --> 00:25:53,355
Very young.

275
00:25:54,895 --> 00:25:55,925
How young?

276
00:25:56,195 --> 00:25:57,195
She'll basically be...

277
00:25:58,165 --> 00:25:59,225
young enough to be your daughter.

278
00:26:09,135 --> 00:26:10,905
What more could I possibly ask for?

279
00:26:19,145 --> 00:26:21,015
- Doctor Shin.
- Hey, James.

280
00:26:21,155 --> 00:26:22,315
Can I get Momo's number?

281
00:26:23,385 --> 00:26:26,785
- You didn't get to meet her?
- I did, but she left for a shoot.

282
00:26:27,625 --> 00:26:28,825
Really?

283
00:26:29,495 --> 00:26:31,825
She's a top star,
so she's incredibly busy.

284
00:26:32,565 --> 00:26:34,335
Or did she just not like Doctor Shin?

285
00:26:37,765 --> 00:26:40,105
- I'll text you her manager's number.
- Not her manager's.

286
00:26:40,105 --> 00:26:41,205
I want Momo's number.

287
00:26:41,275 --> 00:26:44,245
No way. It was hard enough
just to set up that meeting.

288
00:26:44,375 --> 00:26:46,505
I'm Shin Ju Shin.
I'll take full responsibility.

289
00:26:46,505 --> 00:26:48,045
Whose responsibility isn't the issue.

290
00:26:48,315 --> 00:26:49,975
I'll get in deep trouble with her.
She'll have my hide.

291
00:26:50,175 --> 00:26:52,485
Ha Yong Joong's car has arrived.

292
00:26:53,545 --> 00:26:55,315
Didn't Yong Joong go to Italy?

293
00:26:55,515 --> 00:26:56,515
I thought he did.

294
00:26:58,555 --> 00:27:01,795
You should ask CEO Hyun directly.
That's the best way, I think.

295
00:27:02,355 --> 00:27:03,355
Alright.

296
00:27:17,205 --> 00:27:19,475
- Bye.
- Bye.

297
00:27:25,115 --> 00:27:26,915
- Tomorrow at 11:00 a.m.
- Today...

298
00:27:32,085 --> 00:27:33,695
Did the housekeeper let you in?

299
00:27:33,995 --> 00:27:35,455
Your mother gave me the passcode.

300
00:27:36,055 --> 00:27:37,425
She said she was at an art fair.

301
00:27:39,765 --> 00:27:42,535
I feel a little awkward.
I'm not used to doing this kind of thing.

302
00:27:42,965 --> 00:27:44,035
Then don't.

303
00:27:44,435 --> 00:27:45,835
I don't like flowers.

304
00:27:50,405 --> 00:27:51,945
Believe it or not,
some women don't like them.

305
00:27:54,145 --> 00:27:55,175
Okay, then forget the flowers.

306
00:27:55,575 --> 00:27:56,575
There's nothing I want.

307
00:27:57,245 --> 00:27:58,485
I hate them because they wilt.

308
00:27:58,485 --> 00:28:01,115
The flowers I've thrown out so far
would probably fill a few trucks.

309
00:28:07,395 --> 00:28:08,455
Please see yourself out.

310
00:28:17,235 --> 00:28:19,405
Your mother wouldn't give me
your phone number.

311
00:28:20,065 --> 00:28:22,375
Like I said, I'm a mama's girl.

312
00:28:22,375 --> 00:28:24,205
I need my mom's permission for everything.

313
00:28:28,145 --> 00:28:29,415
And I'm really tired.

314
00:28:30,445 --> 00:28:31,685
Then I'll just walk you to your door.

315
00:28:45,325 --> 00:28:47,335
I thought all women liked flowers.

316
00:28:47,795 --> 00:28:49,495
You've only dated that type, then.

317
00:29:03,245 --> 00:29:04,245
Isn't he leaving?

318
00:29:07,615 --> 00:29:08,915
You're just as I expected.

319
00:29:09,115 --> 00:29:10,625
I figured you'd be prickly.

320
00:29:11,325 --> 00:29:13,625
- That's a first.
- They probably just don't say it...

321
00:29:13,625 --> 00:29:14,895
to your face.

322
00:29:16,725 --> 00:29:19,195
I've never really been
that interested in women.

323
00:29:19,265 --> 00:29:20,565
And I don't care.

324
00:29:21,435 --> 00:29:22,735
That sounds like a line from a TV show.

325
00:29:22,735 --> 00:29:24,465
But don't TV shows reflect reality?

326
00:29:24,535 --> 00:29:26,505
What, you think that's a good thing?

327
00:29:26,505 --> 00:29:27,605
A good thing?

328
00:29:27,675 --> 00:29:31,245
Are you proud
ff not being interested in women?

329
00:29:31,875 --> 00:29:34,615
I'm sick and tired of getting attention.

330
00:29:35,175 --> 00:29:36,175
Well then.

331
00:29:43,685 --> 00:29:45,185
Let's be more honest next time.

332
00:29:45,685 --> 00:29:46,725
Emotionally.

333
00:29:53,895 --> 00:29:56,895
- I'd like to get married.
- To whom? Me?

334
00:29:57,305 --> 00:29:58,305
Yes.

335
00:29:59,005 --> 00:30:01,305
- All of a sudden?
- Give me the time and a chance.

336
00:30:01,505 --> 00:30:02,505
I'll earn it.

337
00:30:04,075 --> 00:30:07,315
You think that was honest?
It wasn't at all.

338
00:30:07,375 --> 00:30:09,845
- You're being impulsive.
- I've never been called that before.

339
00:30:09,915 --> 00:30:11,515
Who would say that to your face?

340
00:30:14,985 --> 00:30:17,085
I'll pretend you didn't mean
that I looked easy.

341
00:30:18,625 --> 00:30:19,625
Quite the opposite.

342
00:30:21,425 --> 00:30:22,425
Please leave.

343
00:30:23,755 --> 00:30:27,865
I'll forget this ever happened,
so you don't have to regret it.

344
00:30:28,295 --> 00:30:30,095
I won't ever regret this.

345
00:30:32,105 --> 00:30:33,365
I never have.

346
00:30:33,565 --> 00:30:34,975
You never know.

347
00:30:36,435 --> 00:30:37,945
There is someone I am seeing.

348
00:30:38,205 --> 00:30:40,005
But in your interview, you said otherwise.

349
00:30:40,405 --> 00:30:42,015
And you're not the type to lie, are you?

350
00:30:43,175 --> 00:30:45,245
I do sometimes to reporters.

351
00:30:46,915 --> 00:30:48,085
Have you eaten anything?

352
00:30:48,785 --> 00:30:50,015
A few bites of kimbap.

353
00:30:50,155 --> 00:30:51,885
Then let me order you
something to eat before I go.

354
00:30:51,955 --> 00:30:53,455
You think an actress
would eat late at night?

355
00:30:53,525 --> 00:30:54,795
Aren't actors people too?

356
00:30:54,995 --> 00:30:57,625
Your work just puts food on the table.

357
00:30:57,995 --> 00:30:59,025
So stop that.

358
00:30:59,865 --> 00:31:01,495
You don't have to starve yourself
for this job.

359
00:31:01,695 --> 00:31:04,935
Says the man who got that body
by only eating chicken and vegetables.

360
00:31:06,605 --> 00:31:08,835
I eat everything. I'm not a picky eater.

361
00:31:09,405 --> 00:31:11,145
I thank my parents for my metabolism.

362
00:31:11,145 --> 00:31:12,175
Must be nice.

363
00:31:13,805 --> 00:31:15,075
At least have some fruit
before you go to bed.

364
00:31:17,615 --> 00:31:18,645
You don't have any?

365
00:31:19,785 --> 00:31:21,085
Want me to go buy you some?

366
00:31:22,185 --> 00:31:23,515
I'm not allowed to keep any in the house.

367
00:31:24,855 --> 00:31:26,885
- CEO Hyun?
- Me.

368
00:31:29,025 --> 00:31:30,255
Because you're worried you'll eat it?

369
00:31:31,165 --> 00:31:32,225
Yes.

370
00:31:33,465 --> 00:31:36,135
That's kind of sad.
Though I'm sure you don't see it that way.

371
00:31:36,535 --> 00:31:37,735
(I do feel sorry for myself.)

372
00:31:37,805 --> 00:31:39,165
I do feel sorry for myself.

373
00:31:45,975 --> 00:31:48,615
Even if you were divorced,
I'd still want to marry you.

374
00:31:54,585 --> 00:31:56,515
Even if you were dating ten other guys,

375
00:31:57,055 --> 00:31:58,185
I wouldn't care.

376
00:32:02,195 --> 00:32:03,195
I'll see you again.

377
00:32:05,095 --> 00:32:07,595
Why do you keep switching
to informal speech?

378
00:32:11,735 --> 00:32:14,035
Give them to me.
If you're just going to throw them out.

379
00:32:15,435 --> 00:32:16,435
I'm not throwing them out.

380
00:32:34,255 --> 00:32:36,295
I'm not drawn to your fame or your looks.

381
00:32:36,855 --> 00:32:39,565
I heard from my father that
you were CEO Hyun's daughter,

382
00:32:39,565 --> 00:32:41,665
but I wasn't the least bit interested.

383
00:32:49,375 --> 00:32:50,575
The 20th floor.

384
00:32:51,105 --> 00:32:52,705
This can't be your place.

385
00:32:53,275 --> 00:32:54,345
It's my father's.

386
00:32:56,045 --> 00:32:57,545
But I thought he passed away.

387
00:32:57,685 --> 00:32:59,085
At least, that's what I heard...

388
00:32:59,345 --> 00:33:01,415
when you were nine.

389
00:33:03,385 --> 00:33:04,985
An Hee told me.

390
00:33:05,485 --> 00:33:07,025
You remember all that?

391
00:33:07,895 --> 00:33:09,225
So much for trying to mess with you.

392
00:33:15,035 --> 00:33:16,035
Goodness.

393
00:33:16,765 --> 00:33:17,765
My goodness.

394
00:33:20,035 --> 00:33:21,035
You know her?

395
00:34:12,585 --> 00:34:13,755
You're just getting in?

396
00:34:14,455 --> 00:34:16,295
I thought I told you
not to buy this stuff.

397
00:34:16,655 --> 00:34:17,895
You found that?

398
00:34:17,965 --> 00:34:20,025
I get indigestion every now and then.

399
00:34:22,495 --> 00:34:23,895
Could that be your mom?

400
00:34:25,365 --> 00:34:28,235
- An early morning delivery?
- But do they ring the doorbell?

401
00:34:28,405 --> 00:34:31,505
Oh, right. It must be a fan.

402
00:34:32,405 --> 00:34:33,845
But there's no one there.

403
00:34:34,915 --> 00:34:35,915
Go and check.

404
00:34:43,985 --> 00:34:45,425
Who would leave this...

405
00:34:46,525 --> 00:34:48,295
You didn't order this, did you?

406
00:34:49,995 --> 00:34:51,595
Did a fan leave it?

407
00:34:51,925 --> 00:34:53,865
But how'd they get in?

408
00:34:55,135 --> 00:34:56,835
Gosh, my bladder's about to burst.

409
00:35:01,335 --> 00:35:02,535
(Greek yogurt)

410
00:35:02,605 --> 00:35:04,145
(Milk wafer ice cream)

411
00:36:01,835 --> 00:36:03,135
He's decent, I'll give him that.

412
00:36:04,335 --> 00:36:05,865
Looks aren't everything.

413
00:36:06,935 --> 00:36:08,735
So, does that apply to me too?

414
00:36:09,405 --> 00:36:11,175
Why'd you give him the code
to the front gate?

415
00:36:11,175 --> 00:36:13,005
He's not just some random person.

416
00:36:13,475 --> 00:36:16,075
He's Professor Shin's son.
How could I not?

417
00:36:17,145 --> 00:36:20,315
Moon So Young reads her scripts
just fine without glasses.

418
00:36:20,715 --> 00:36:22,185
She's seven years older than you, Mom.

419
00:36:22,385 --> 00:36:24,255
And she's single with no kids.

420
00:36:24,525 --> 00:36:26,055
What does being single have to do
with her eyesight?

421
00:36:26,685 --> 00:36:28,725
Enjoy your acting career with no regrets.

422
00:36:28,725 --> 00:36:30,255
You can get married in about ten years.

423
00:36:30,425 --> 00:36:32,665
- You think he'll wait for me?
- Not him, someone else.

424
00:36:32,725 --> 00:36:34,665
All the good ones will be taken by then.

425
00:36:35,065 --> 00:36:36,495
What about someone
five or six years younger?

426
00:36:37,565 --> 00:36:39,535
After I married your father,

427
00:36:40,035 --> 00:36:42,035
people thought I was 50
before I went under the knife.

428
00:36:42,175 --> 00:36:43,575
Mom, honestly.

429
00:36:45,275 --> 00:36:47,615
The way plastic surgery is advancing here,

430
00:36:48,075 --> 00:36:49,845
maybe there won't be any old people left.

431
00:36:51,085 --> 00:36:52,545
That's a real possibility.

432
00:36:53,145 --> 00:36:56,685
Nothing's wrong with aging gracefully
as a glamorous actress.

433
00:36:56,785 --> 00:36:58,025
- Seriously?
- Yes.

434
00:36:58,025 --> 00:36:59,885
Says the woman who lived a happy life.

435
00:37:00,255 --> 00:37:01,825
I was happy.

436
00:37:02,155 --> 00:37:03,295
But...

437
00:37:05,125 --> 00:37:07,635
If he contacts you, shut him down.
Don't give him any false hope.

438
00:37:08,095 --> 00:37:09,265
Don't lead him on.

439
00:37:13,265 --> 00:37:14,275
Who is it?

440
00:37:14,275 --> 00:37:15,635
I'm from Noir Hospital.

441
00:37:15,775 --> 00:37:17,675
I'm on an errand
for Doctor Shin Ju Shin, head of surgery.

442
00:37:18,775 --> 00:37:20,275
The doors are opening.

443
00:37:30,485 --> 00:37:31,625
Here.

444
00:37:36,295 --> 00:37:37,355
(The passcode is the first 3 digits
of your front gate code.)

445
00:37:37,355 --> 00:37:38,965
The passcode is the first 3 digits
of your front gate code.

446
00:37:58,545 --> 00:38:01,115
I kept the flowers
and arranged them nicely.

447
00:38:01,415 --> 00:38:04,255
I chose them carefully
while thinking of you.

448
00:38:06,185 --> 00:38:08,825
My mother passed away five years ago.

449
00:38:09,695 --> 00:38:13,565
She left this for me to give to the person
I fall in love with.

450
00:38:14,735 --> 00:38:15,865
I wanted to express...

451
00:38:16,395 --> 00:38:18,365
my sincere feelings,

452
00:38:18,935 --> 00:38:20,705
and it had to be something meaningful.

453
00:38:21,405 --> 00:38:23,735
No matter how hard I thought,
this was all I could think of.

454
00:38:24,705 --> 00:38:25,905
With no strings attached,

455
00:38:26,445 --> 00:38:28,245
I hope you'll accept it
without feeling any pressure.

456
00:38:52,665 --> 00:38:55,035
I didn't admit any new patients yesterday.

457
00:38:55,035 --> 00:38:57,235
But we did get two calls,

458
00:38:57,305 --> 00:38:59,005
one was for orthopedics,

459
00:38:59,075 --> 00:39:02,315
and the other didn't seem to be
a major trauma case.

460
00:39:02,575 --> 00:39:05,585
We got a call from emergency services
in Gangnam at around 11:00 p.m.

461
00:39:05,645 --> 00:39:10,015
A woman in her 30s fell in the street
and started vomiting blood.

462
00:39:10,085 --> 00:39:14,225
It sounded like a viral syndrome,
so I told them to contact the ER.

463
00:39:15,025 --> 00:39:17,355
Her ankle and toes were crushed.

464
00:39:17,425 --> 00:39:19,665
But the ankle was the only major damage.

465
00:39:19,725 --> 00:39:20,995
But the confusing part is this.

466
00:39:21,295 --> 00:39:23,465
There's this mark on the frontal lobe.

467
00:39:23,595 --> 00:39:25,235
I'm wondering if it could be a hemorrhage.

468
00:39:25,305 --> 00:39:26,735
That's calcification.

469
00:39:26,805 --> 00:39:27,835
(Calcification)

470
00:39:34,915 --> 00:39:36,445
Mornings are when I'm happiest.

471
00:39:36,945 --> 00:39:38,545
It's the one time
I can actually eat something.

472
00:39:39,145 --> 00:39:40,385
Is it that hard for you?

473
00:39:40,445 --> 00:39:41,855
You said it was hard for everyone.

474
00:39:42,115 --> 00:39:43,555
When filming eating scenes,

475
00:39:43,615 --> 00:39:45,285
other actors just fake it,

476
00:39:45,285 --> 00:39:46,755
but I actually eat for real.

477
00:39:47,685 --> 00:39:48,995
I'm completely starving!

478
00:39:48,995 --> 00:39:52,395
Seriously, you aced that eating scene
in 'A Maiden's Prayer."

479
00:39:55,835 --> 00:39:57,365
Is that my ring?

480
00:39:57,835 --> 00:39:58,905
It's not yours.

481
00:40:01,505 --> 00:40:03,335
- It was a gift.
- Who from?

482
00:40:03,535 --> 00:40:05,175
Not Shin Ju Shin, right?

483
00:40:08,345 --> 00:40:09,375
Was it from him?

484
00:40:12,515 --> 00:40:14,485
Why did you accept it?
I told you to cut him off completely.

485
00:40:17,755 --> 00:40:18,785
For goodness sake.

486
00:40:19,685 --> 00:40:21,395
He's really determined, isn't he?

487
00:40:22,395 --> 00:40:24,495
He's really counting his chickens
before they hatch.

488
00:40:26,395 --> 00:40:27,625
But you're not going to let...

489
00:40:27,625 --> 00:40:29,165
something as little as this sway you,
are you?

490
00:40:29,395 --> 00:40:30,595
This isn't little.

491
00:40:30,595 --> 00:40:32,305
You'll never get its worth if you sell it.

492
00:40:32,435 --> 00:40:33,835
Send it back to him now.

493
00:40:37,845 --> 00:40:39,005
What time is Manager Oh getting here?

494
00:40:40,105 --> 00:40:41,105
What if something happens in transit?

495
00:40:45,945 --> 00:40:48,385
It's not a difficult surgery,
so please try to relax.

496
00:40:49,455 --> 00:40:50,455
Okay, thank you.

497
00:40:55,695 --> 00:40:57,995
Momo is here to see you, Doctor.

498
00:41:00,995 --> 00:41:03,165
- Any patients waiting?
- There are two left.

499
00:41:04,935 --> 00:41:07,005
- Tell her to wait for a bit.
- You want Momo to wait?

500
00:41:07,005 --> 00:41:08,805
- Yes.
- Okay.

501
00:41:17,475 --> 00:41:19,985
(Department of Neurosurgery,
Angiography Room)

502
00:41:21,215 --> 00:41:22,215
You can go in now.

503
00:41:27,385 --> 00:41:29,655
(Shin Ju Shin, Neurosurgeon)

504
00:41:44,505 --> 00:41:45,745
I'm sorry I don't have anything
to offer you.

505
00:41:46,275 --> 00:41:47,545
I'm here to return this.

506
00:41:49,945 --> 00:41:51,145
It's too much.

507
00:41:51,345 --> 00:41:53,785
Have you never given someone a gift
just from the heart?

508
00:41:54,445 --> 00:41:55,455
I have.

509
00:41:56,655 --> 00:41:58,555
- And?
- This isn't that.

510
00:41:58,885 --> 00:42:01,795
A gift from the heart shouldn't have
an ulterior motive.

511
00:42:02,355 --> 00:42:04,725
Are interest and attraction
considered motives?

512
00:42:10,365 --> 00:42:11,765
Your highest level of education is
a high school graduate.

513
00:42:16,575 --> 00:42:19,505
That's if you don't go back
to theater and film at Korea University.

514
00:42:23,745 --> 00:42:25,245
My mother was also a high school graduate.

515
00:42:25,915 --> 00:42:28,915
She was in her sophomore year of college
when she married my father.

516
00:42:31,115 --> 00:42:32,625
And she had me when she was 23.

517
00:42:34,695 --> 00:42:37,255
She was a very affectionate
and wise woman.

518
00:42:41,065 --> 00:42:43,865
When I lie down to sleep,
I'd always picture my mother's face,

519
00:42:49,105 --> 00:42:50,835
but now, there's someone else
I picture too.

520
00:43:00,845 --> 00:43:03,115
- I want to share my whole life with you.
- But, I don't.

521
00:43:03,185 --> 00:43:05,185
- I'm asking for a chance.
- Does what I want not matter?

522
00:43:06,055 --> 00:43:07,055
I'll scream.

523
00:43:07,425 --> 00:43:09,355
You must've heard that
you're like an onion a lot.

524
00:43:15,665 --> 00:43:17,165
Peeling back each layer
reveals something new.

525
00:43:17,495 --> 00:43:18,565
That's just your fantasy.

526
00:43:19,565 --> 00:43:20,865
What you see isn't everything.

527
00:43:21,835 --> 00:43:23,505
I like a woman with substance.

528
00:43:24,105 --> 00:43:26,545
There must be many women with substance
working here as doctors.

529
00:43:26,605 --> 00:43:28,645
I'm not talking about book-smart fools
who think their degree is everything.

530
00:43:30,115 --> 00:43:31,115
Someone with love...

531
00:43:33,915 --> 00:43:35,285
and compassion...

532
00:43:36,955 --> 00:43:37,955
in their heart.

533
00:43:41,595 --> 00:43:42,695
I'm not compassionate.

534
00:43:50,465 --> 00:43:51,465
But I can feel it.

535
00:43:52,065 --> 00:43:53,335
I can't help what I feel.

536
00:43:54,265 --> 00:43:55,905
You're always on my mind.

537
00:43:56,935 --> 00:43:58,345
How do I get you out of my head?

538
00:43:58,975 --> 00:44:00,345
If you know how, why don't you tell me?

539
00:44:00,605 --> 00:44:01,975
Are your feelings the only ones
that matter?

540
00:44:02,645 --> 00:44:04,175
And what about how the other person feels?

541
00:44:04,915 --> 00:44:07,345
If you've become a top actress
by starving yourself,

542
00:44:07,345 --> 00:44:08,355
isn't that enough?

543
00:44:09,285 --> 00:44:12,525
Study, or do whatever else you want,

544
00:44:13,055 --> 00:44:15,525
eat to your heart's content,
and pack on the pounds.

545
00:44:16,395 --> 00:44:18,395
Because I'll love you
even if your whole body jiggles.

546
00:44:20,125 --> 00:44:21,125
Just don't let your brain get fat.

547
00:44:27,165 --> 00:44:28,405
I'll become your everything.

548
00:44:29,575 --> 00:44:31,135
I can promise you. I swear it.

549
00:44:32,845 --> 00:44:34,205
I'm confident I can be...

550
00:44:35,875 --> 00:44:36,875
a responsible husband.

551
00:44:38,745 --> 00:44:40,485
As husband and wife,

552
00:44:42,115 --> 00:44:44,015
let's live an ordinary life together.

553
00:44:46,185 --> 00:44:47,255
What's so complicated about love?

554
00:44:50,795 --> 00:44:51,825
(Dad)

555
00:44:56,365 --> 00:44:57,595
It's my dad. I have to take this.

556
00:45:01,105 --> 00:45:02,775
(Dad)

557
00:45:04,845 --> 00:45:05,845
Yes, Director.

558
00:45:08,915 --> 00:45:09,915
No, I can't.

559
00:45:11,145 --> 00:45:13,245
The mother of an acquaintance
is on her way to the ER.

560
00:45:24,025 --> 00:45:25,025
Hello.

561
00:45:25,525 --> 00:45:26,525
Oh, my.

562
00:45:28,235 --> 00:45:29,995
Are you here with Professor Shin?

563
00:45:29,995 --> 00:45:31,465
My father has dinner plans.

564
00:45:32,635 --> 00:45:33,735
If you're not meeting anyone...

565
00:45:34,465 --> 00:45:35,705
I'm not. Have a seat.

566
00:45:42,315 --> 00:45:45,385
So this is how you stay in shape?

567
00:45:47,085 --> 00:45:48,085
I hardly ever get to come.

568
00:45:49,585 --> 00:45:52,855
My Momo just loves the ocean.

569
00:45:54,555 --> 00:45:57,895
Since I have you here,
there's something I'd like to discuss.

570
00:45:59,295 --> 00:46:01,165
I'd like to start dating Momo seriously.

571
00:46:02,895 --> 00:46:04,805
And what did Momo say?

572
00:46:06,005 --> 00:46:08,835
- She turned me down.
- Oh, my. Did she?

573
00:46:09,135 --> 00:46:11,075
She said she's seeing someone,
but it feels like an excuse.

574
00:46:11,905 --> 00:46:13,445
Maybe it's not an excuse.

575
00:46:14,245 --> 00:46:16,045
She's so busy,
she barely has time to breathe.

576
00:46:16,445 --> 00:46:18,385
Besides her staff,

577
00:46:18,385 --> 00:46:20,945
she's drifted apart
from the few friends she had.

578
00:46:23,285 --> 00:46:25,125
As her mother,
it breaks my heart sometimes.

579
00:46:26,125 --> 00:46:27,555
She's at an age
when she should be out having fun.

580
00:46:29,725 --> 00:46:31,565
And what does Professor Shin think?

581
00:46:31,895 --> 00:46:33,225
I haven't told him yet.

582
00:46:33,965 --> 00:46:35,795
I was hoping you could help me, CEO Hyun.

583
00:46:37,335 --> 00:46:39,835
I'm all for it, especially since it's you.

584
00:46:41,875 --> 00:46:43,775
I have a meeting
at the Chinese restaurant here.

585
00:46:47,375 --> 00:46:51,845
But I wonder
if Professor Shin will approve.

586
00:46:52,115 --> 00:46:53,585
My father always respects my decisions.

587
00:46:54,345 --> 00:46:55,555
Besides, you two are close, aren't you?

588
00:46:57,285 --> 00:46:58,885
That's a separate issue
from our friendship.

589
00:46:59,655 --> 00:47:00,685
I'll see you around.

590
00:47:01,085 --> 00:47:02,195
Yes.

591
00:48:00,745 --> 00:48:03,585
(Nua General Hospital)

592
00:48:22,405 --> 00:48:25,375
(You have a visitor.)

593
00:48:26,675 --> 00:48:27,675
Who is it?

594
00:48:28,415 --> 00:48:29,415
Yes.

595
00:48:32,185 --> 00:48:33,185
Right this way.

596
00:49:14,425 --> 00:49:15,425
Hey.

597
00:49:23,765 --> 00:49:25,365
I didn't realize
you'd already left for the day.

598
00:49:26,065 --> 00:49:29,135
I wanted to say hello to the Director,
but it's hard to get a moment with him.

599
00:49:30,535 --> 00:49:32,705
What do you mean?
I'm sure he'd be glad to see you.

600
00:49:37,675 --> 00:49:39,515
There's one for the Director in there too.

601
00:49:40,315 --> 00:49:41,715
I just got a full-time position.

602
00:49:42,755 --> 00:49:44,455
I brought a little something.

603
00:49:47,725 --> 00:49:48,725
The thought is more than enough.

604
00:49:53,865 --> 00:49:56,595
I'll tell him you stopped by to say hi.

605
00:49:57,795 --> 00:49:58,805
Where did you end up?

606
00:49:59,935 --> 00:50:01,035
Lim Company.

607
00:50:01,305 --> 00:50:03,305
You mean James's company?

608
00:50:03,975 --> 00:50:06,475
Yes. I just finished
my two-year internship there.

609
00:50:08,815 --> 00:50:10,675
Take it back, whatever it is.

610
00:50:13,145 --> 00:50:14,245
I can't return it.

611
00:50:14,685 --> 00:50:15,815
Didn't you get it at a department store?

612
00:50:17,215 --> 00:50:18,725
It's been over a week.

613
00:50:19,285 --> 00:50:21,685
It's not much, but please accept it.

614
00:50:28,195 --> 00:50:29,195
Stop licking your lips.

615
00:50:29,635 --> 00:50:32,005
They say people who lick their lips
are insincere.

616
00:50:36,005 --> 00:50:37,235
But that's not true for me.

617
00:50:42,315 --> 00:50:43,845
And who gave you permission
to get married?

618
00:50:44,145 --> 00:50:45,515
Do I need your permission to get married?

619
00:50:46,485 --> 00:50:48,455
I'm 24. It's the perfect age to marry.

620
00:50:48,455 --> 00:50:50,685
The "perfect age" now is 33 or 34.

621
00:50:51,155 --> 00:50:53,625
How many times have you even seen him?
You two haven't even dated.

622
00:50:53,685 --> 00:50:55,895
Mom, you told me you and Dad got married
just six months after you met.

623
00:50:57,695 --> 00:50:59,625
You're just hitting your stride
as an actress,

624
00:50:59,895 --> 00:51:02,135
and you can stay at the top
for at least another ten years.

625
00:51:02,395 --> 00:51:03,865
What makes you think marriage is so great?

626
00:51:04,195 --> 00:51:06,065
I'll never know if it's good or bad
until I try it.

627
00:51:06,635 --> 00:51:09,505
You're young.
Have fun and play the field a bit.

628
00:51:09,705 --> 00:51:11,175
Do I even have the time to have fun
and play around?

629
00:51:13,005 --> 00:51:16,275
There's no one else like him.
I'll regret it if I lose him.

630
00:51:16,615 --> 00:51:18,145
There are plenty of fish in the sea.

631
00:51:18,215 --> 00:51:20,315
And how many of those
are actually worth it?

632
00:51:20,945 --> 00:51:22,215
And what guarantee do I have...

633
00:51:22,215 --> 00:51:24,815
that I'll ever find another decent guy
I'm compatible with?

634
00:51:25,325 --> 00:51:28,085
- But you should see more people...
- I've made up my mind.

635
00:51:28,325 --> 00:51:29,455
What about me?

636
00:51:29,455 --> 00:51:31,895
If I marry, do we become strangers?

637
00:51:34,265 --> 00:51:37,195
Would you rather I stay single
and grow old by your side forever?

638
00:51:38,135 --> 00:51:40,805
Shin Ju Shin is 33. I'm 46.

639
00:51:41,465 --> 00:51:43,135
That's only a 13-year age gap.

640
00:51:43,135 --> 00:51:44,475
A son-in-law 13 years younger than me?

641
00:51:44,705 --> 00:51:46,875
The very thought is unsettling.
It's humiliating.

642
00:51:46,945 --> 00:51:49,045
I want to get married soon
and start a family right away.

643
00:51:51,515 --> 00:51:52,985
I grew up alone, and I was so lonely.

644
00:51:52,985 --> 00:51:54,085
I'm going to have 2, maybe 3 kids.

645
00:51:54,615 --> 00:51:56,115
You expect me to be a grandmother
at my age?

646
00:52:04,225 --> 00:52:05,225
Thank you.

647
00:52:05,965 --> 00:52:07,095
Please, feel free to speak comfortably.

648
00:52:07,665 --> 00:52:08,665
All in good time.

649
00:52:09,365 --> 00:52:11,165
What did your father have to say?

650
00:52:12,065 --> 00:52:13,065
He's happy, of course.

651
00:52:16,935 --> 00:52:18,175
Not that outfit.

652
00:52:18,805 --> 00:52:21,005
On a day like today,
you should've dressed up a little.

653
00:52:26,085 --> 00:52:27,815
Given your father's disposition,

654
00:52:27,945 --> 00:52:30,615
I don't think he'd like a daughter-in-law
who's an entertainer.

655
00:52:30,785 --> 00:52:31,885
Not at all.

656
00:52:32,525 --> 00:52:34,085
He was very happy and supportive.

657
00:52:41,795 --> 00:52:44,335
Do you really have to steal my Momo
away from me?

658
00:52:45,065 --> 00:52:46,135
I'm sorry.

659
00:52:46,565 --> 00:52:48,635
Think of it as gaining a son,
not losing a daughter.

660
00:52:50,105 --> 00:52:51,945
Honestly, what's the rush?

661
00:52:51,945 --> 00:52:53,305
You could just date for a few years.

662
00:52:53,905 --> 00:52:55,515
Momo still has a lot of endorsement deals.

663
00:52:56,945 --> 00:52:58,515
They said it was not a breach of contract.

664
00:52:59,085 --> 00:53:00,415
I consulted a lawyer,

665
00:53:00,715 --> 00:53:02,755
and the agency thinks it could be good
for her image.

666
00:53:03,815 --> 00:53:04,815
You've heard that as well, right?

667
00:53:07,885 --> 00:53:11,025
How about an engagement first?

668
00:53:13,565 --> 00:53:15,965
- Mr. Kim, the driver, is here.
- Okay.

669
00:53:18,435 --> 00:53:19,505
Let me see your hand.

670
00:53:21,435 --> 00:53:22,535
You can read palms?

671
00:53:26,605 --> 00:53:28,175
It's not an exact science, but...

672
00:53:29,375 --> 00:53:31,575
Momo's father passed away far too young.

673
00:53:53,435 --> 00:53:54,435
What?

674
00:53:55,235 --> 00:53:56,235
Staff Sergeant.

675
00:53:59,345 --> 00:54:00,505
Staff...

676
00:54:14,755 --> 00:54:15,795
Listen up, Geum Ba Ra.

677
00:54:16,155 --> 00:54:18,965
Things like what happened today
are going to keep happening.

678
00:54:19,825 --> 00:54:21,265
In two years, I'll be gone from here too.

679
00:54:21,725 --> 00:54:24,065
Only you can protect yourself.
So what are you going to do?

680
00:54:24,865 --> 00:54:26,435
When you're pushed around,
are you going to take the money...

681
00:54:26,505 --> 00:54:28,605
and go buy some stupid snacks
and cry about it?

682
00:54:31,505 --> 00:54:32,645
The crying stops today.

683
00:54:33,605 --> 00:54:35,945
You're 11 years old.
You're too old to cry so easily.

684
00:54:39,215 --> 00:54:40,445
From now on,
eat even if you don't want to.

685
00:54:41,145 --> 00:54:43,955
Force it down with water if you have to.
That's how you'll grow.

686
00:54:44,285 --> 00:54:47,725
You're an orphan. If you're weak,
middle school will make this seem easy.

687
00:54:47,985 --> 00:54:49,625
It'll just be kids looking down on you
and picking on you.

688
00:54:50,355 --> 00:54:51,355
You have to endure it.

689
00:54:52,895 --> 00:54:54,625
You could even get abducted by bad people.

690
00:54:58,835 --> 00:55:00,735
I'm going to teach you
how to protect yourself.

691
00:55:01,705 --> 00:55:03,105
So are you going to learn or not?

692
00:55:07,805 --> 00:55:08,815
Harder.

693
00:55:09,815 --> 00:55:11,215
I can't feel a thing. Harder.

694
00:55:11,275 --> 00:55:12,415
Harder.

695
00:55:14,085 --> 00:55:15,085
Harder!

696
00:55:27,965 --> 00:55:29,095
- Darn it.
- Hey!

697
00:55:31,495 --> 00:55:32,535
Hey, I said let go!

698
00:55:41,905 --> 00:55:44,215
Darn it! Hey, you!

699
00:55:46,745 --> 00:55:47,745
Hey!

700
00:55:51,085 --> 00:55:52,585
Why, you...

701
00:55:52,925 --> 00:55:53,925
Ba Ra!

702
00:55:54,255 --> 00:55:55,255
Hey!

703
00:56:02,995 --> 00:56:03,995
Shoot!

704
00:56:12,545 --> 00:56:13,545
What?

705
00:56:20,515 --> 00:56:21,545
Darn it.

706
00:56:29,625 --> 00:56:31,155
- You brats!
- Darn it.

707
00:56:32,055 --> 00:56:33,065
Get up.

708
00:56:38,805 --> 00:56:40,535
I'm letting you off the hook this time.

709
00:56:41,305 --> 00:56:42,505
Don't try anything like this again.

710
00:56:43,675 --> 00:56:45,135
It won't be pretty next time.

711
00:56:48,175 --> 00:56:50,145
Life's too short for this.

712
00:56:50,645 --> 00:56:54,045
Why live like demons
when there are better things to do?

713
00:56:54,945 --> 00:56:56,415
The way you act is evil.

714
00:57:03,425 --> 00:57:05,395
You filthy orphans!

715
00:57:18,975 --> 00:57:19,975
What did you say?

716
00:57:22,545 --> 00:57:23,545
I didn't quite...

717
00:57:24,375 --> 00:57:25,375
hear you.

718
00:57:26,785 --> 00:57:28,485
You're orphans, aren't you?

719
00:57:42,695 --> 00:57:44,695
We don't have anyone to protect us.

720
00:57:45,635 --> 00:57:47,765
Remember, you'll be expelled
for the slightest bit of trouble.

721
00:57:48,935 --> 00:57:51,875
Unless they attack you first,
don't hurt anyone.

722
00:57:56,545 --> 00:57:57,575
Someday,

723
00:57:58,345 --> 00:58:00,015
you're going to regret this.

724
00:58:01,545 --> 00:58:03,655
You'll be the one crying, not me.

725
00:58:04,415 --> 00:58:05,685
Maybe even tears of blood.

726
00:58:11,025 --> 00:58:13,195
What are you, a psychic now?

727
00:58:23,335 --> 00:58:24,635
How disgusting.

728
00:58:25,645 --> 00:58:28,805
Who are you to lecture me
when you weren't even raised right?

729
00:58:31,875 --> 00:58:34,885
I'll teach that tramp a real lesson
one of these days.

730
00:58:35,215 --> 00:58:37,215
I didn't brush my teeth today.

731
00:58:37,615 --> 00:58:38,885
Hey, Geum Ba Ra!

732
00:58:39,355 --> 00:58:41,355
Ashes, ashes, Ba Ra falls down.

733
00:58:43,655 --> 00:58:45,695
Aren't you curious about the parents
who abandoned you?

734
00:58:46,125 --> 00:58:48,725
If I were you,
I'd search all the mountain temples.

735
00:58:56,575 --> 00:58:57,635
Babe!

736
00:58:59,375 --> 00:59:00,975
Hey, what happened to your face?

737
00:59:01,175 --> 00:59:02,175
I got hit.

738
00:59:02,875 --> 00:59:03,875
Who was it?

739
00:59:04,445 --> 00:59:05,445
A guy?

740
00:59:05,945 --> 00:59:06,945
A girl.

741
00:59:15,755 --> 00:59:18,655
Hey, you piece of trash.
How dare you scar my girl's face?

742
00:59:19,195 --> 00:59:20,265
Keep your eyes down...

743
00:59:20,795 --> 00:59:21,795
with respect.

744
00:59:22,265 --> 00:59:23,595
She needs to be taught a lesson.

745
00:59:24,065 --> 00:59:25,805
- A proper one.
- Strip her.

746
00:59:36,875 --> 00:59:38,815
- Do something.
- Darn it.

747
00:59:44,185 --> 00:59:45,185
Take that!

748
00:59:56,865 --> 00:59:57,895
Darn it.

749
00:59:58,235 --> 00:59:59,505
Hey, hold her down.

750
01:00:09,215 --> 01:00:10,215
What is this, a girdle?

751
01:00:13,985 --> 01:00:16,115
Gosh, that's awesome.

752
01:00:17,315 --> 01:00:18,915
Look at that definition.

753
01:00:18,985 --> 01:00:20,885
You could do your laundry on these abs.

754
01:00:22,185 --> 01:00:24,795
They might look soft,
but they're as hard as a grindstone.

755
01:00:25,195 --> 01:00:27,595
You could really grind on these.

756
01:00:30,165 --> 01:00:31,535
Instead of working your thighs out
at night,

757
01:00:32,095 --> 01:00:33,105
have you been training your abs?

758
01:00:33,835 --> 01:00:35,735
What are you doing?

759
01:00:36,005 --> 01:00:38,735
- Take my girl home safely.
- Babe!

760
01:01:04,595 --> 01:01:05,835
Hey, stomp her!

761
01:01:08,765 --> 01:01:09,775
Darn it.

762
01:01:21,685 --> 01:01:22,855
Hey, move out of the way.

763
01:01:25,585 --> 01:01:27,255
Today is a turning point in your life.

764
01:01:28,555 --> 01:01:30,995
I'm going to make a woman out of you.

765
01:01:46,805 --> 01:01:48,945
Hey...

766
01:02:12,735 --> 01:02:13,735
An Hee.

767
01:02:15,565 --> 01:02:17,305
You don't have to worry about me anymore.

768
01:02:18,835 --> 01:02:20,375
You can rest easy now.

769
01:02:24,715 --> 01:02:27,945
I'm going to sell this house
and donate the money in your name.

770
01:02:31,015 --> 01:02:32,725
And on the anniversary of your death,
don't forget...

771
01:02:33,685 --> 01:02:34,755
to visit me.

772
01:02:38,195 --> 01:02:39,965
I'll make your favorite...

773
01:02:42,025 --> 01:02:43,495
kimchi fried rice for you.

774
01:02:52,405 --> 01:02:55,705
(Present Day)

775
01:03:08,755 --> 01:03:10,025
Come here.

776
01:05:36,675 --> 01:05:39,545
(Doctor Shin)

777
01:05:40,345 --> 01:05:41,345
Tell me...

778
01:05:42,375 --> 01:05:44,415
- your name.
- What am I supposed to say?

779
01:05:44,945 --> 01:05:47,985
You know how it's hard to explain
feelings and emotions.

780
01:05:48,585 --> 01:05:51,415
They said Momo fainted while scuba diving,
but I haven't heard anything since.

781
01:05:51,485 --> 01:05:52,755
She hasn't shown up at all.

782
01:05:52,825 --> 01:05:54,185
Do you think Momo is in trouble?

783
01:05:54,255 --> 01:05:55,355
Confusing, isn't it?

784
01:05:55,755 --> 01:05:57,155
You'll get used to it in time.

785
01:05:57,755 --> 01:05:59,255
What's so great about it?

786
01:05:59,525 --> 01:06:00,795
You've never been into anyone, have you?

787
01:06:02,935 --> 01:06:04,935
It was bound to happen, Momo.

788
01:06:05,565 --> 01:06:07,805
Geum Ba Ra,
are you biting the hand that feeds you?

789
01:06:07,935 --> 01:06:11,135
Her phone's been off,
and Jin Ju told me about the accident...

790
01:06:11,505 --> 01:06:13,645
- Excuse me...
- Go ahead.

791
01:06:13,945 --> 01:06:15,275
What's going on? Was it an accident?

792
01:06:16,275 --> 01:06:17,675
Apparently, he's the one who called 911.

793
01:06:21,985 --> 01:06:24,085
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
